Phase 1: Canvas Synthesis (The Killer Feature)

  Problem Statement

  Users build rich context chains on the canvas — connecting nodes, generating AI content, attaching documents — but
  there's no way to harvest that spatial thinking into a coherent output. The canvas is a thinking tool with no
  "finish line." Users think visually but can't produce linearly. This is the #1 gap preventing Eden from being a
  true BASB app.

  Intended Solution

  Let users select any group of connected nodes and trigger AI synthesis that respects the canvas topology —
  producing a coherent summary, argument, or document that understands why those nodes are connected and in what
  order. Output lands as a new "synthesis node" on the canvas, creating a visible artifact of distilled thinking.

  Sub-tasks

  1.1 — Multi-node selection context builder
  - Build buildSynthesisContext(selectedNodeIds: string[]) in a new src/features/canvas/services/synthesisService.ts
  - Walks the subgraph of selected nodes, respects edge direction (parent → child = reasoning flow)
  - Topologically sorts nodes so AI receives them in logical order
  - Includes heading + output + attachment summaries per node
  - Injects KB context (reuse existing getKBContext() budget system)
  - Returns a structured prompt with node relationships made explicit

  1.2 — Synthesis prompt templates
  - Create src/features/ai/prompts/synthesisPrompts.ts
  - Three synthesis modes:
    - Summarize — "Distill these connected ideas into a concise summary"
    - Outline — "Create a structured outline from these ideas, preserving their relationships"
    - Narrative — "Write a coherent document that synthesizes these ideas into a flowing argument"
  - Each template receives the topologically-sorted context and node count
  - String resources in localization (no hardcoded prompts in components)

  1.3 — Synthesis action in canvas UI
  - Add "Synthesize" to the selection toolbar (the bar that appears when multiple nodes are selected)
  - Clicking opens a small popover with the three mode choices (Summarize / Outline / Narrative)
  - Triggers useSynthesis hook → calls Gemini with the built context
  - Creates a new IdeaCard positioned to the right of the selection bounding box
  - New node is auto-connected to all selected nodes with relationship: 'derived'
  - Node heading auto-set to e.g. "Synthesis of 5 ideas" (from string resources)

  1.4 — Synthesis node visual differentiation
  - Add a new colorKey: synthesis (a distinct visual treatment — e.g. gradient border or subtle badge)
  - Synthesis nodes show a small "synthesized from N nodes" footer
  - Clicking the footer highlights the source nodes on canvas (visual trace-back)

  1.5 — TDD test suite
  - synthesisService.test.ts: topological sort, cycle handling, context budget limits
  - useSynthesis.test.ts: hook triggers Gemini, creates node, creates edges
  - SynthesisPopover.test.ts: renders modes, calls hook on selection
  - Structural test: synthesis prompt templates use string resources

