  Phase 2: Branch Export (Canvas → Document)

  Problem Statement

  Canvas thinking is powerful for ideation but useless if you can't turn it into a deliverable. Currently the only
  export is a raw JSON dump. Users need to go from "I figured this out on my canvas" to "here's a document I can
  share/use" without leaving the app. This is BASB's "Express" move — the most underdeveloped part of the app.

  Intended Solution

  Let users select a node and export its entire downstream branch (or any selected subgraph) as a structured markdown
   document. The export follows the canvas topology to determine document structure — parent nodes become sections,
  child nodes become subsections. AI optionally polishes the output into a cohesive document.

  Sub-tasks

  2.1 — Branch traversal service
  - Create src/features/canvas/services/branchExportService.ts
  - collectBranch(rootNodeId: string) — BFS/DFS from root node, follows outgoing edges
  - Returns ordered tree structure: { node, children: BranchNode[] }
  - Handles cycles (mark visited, skip re-visits)
  - Handles disconnected selections (multiple roots → multiple top-level sections)

  2.2 — Tree-to-markdown converter
  - branchToMarkdown(tree: BranchNode[]) — converts branch tree to structured markdown
  - Root node heading → # Title, children → ## Subsections, grandchildren → ### Sub-subsections
  - Node output content preserved as body text under each heading
  - Attachments listed as links/references at section end
  - Images embedded as markdown image references
  - Tags converted to document metadata/frontmatter

  2.3 — AI polish option
  - Optional "Polish with AI" toggle on the export dialog
  - Sends the raw markdown to Gemini with a prompt: "Improve the flow and transitions between sections while
  preserving all content and structure"
  - Returns polished markdown that the user can preview before exporting

  2.4 — Export dialog UI
  - Trigger: Right-click node → "Export branch" OR selection toolbar → "Export"
  - Dialog shows:
    - Preview of the markdown (rendered)
    - Toggle: "Include AI polish"
    - Format selector: Markdown (.md) / Plain text (.txt)
    - "Copy to clipboard" button + "Download" button
  - Component: src/features/canvas/components/ExportDialog.tsx

  2.5 — Single-node export shortcut
  - NodeUtilsBar "Copy" action gets a submenu: "Copy content" (existing) / "Export branch"
  - For leaf nodes with no children, "Export branch" just exports that single node as clean markdown

  2.6 — TDD test suite
  - branchExportService.test.ts: tree traversal, cycle detection, multi-root handling
  - branchToMarkdown.test.ts: heading levels, content formatting, attachment references
  - ExportDialog.test.ts: render preview, toggle polish, download triggers
  - Structural test: no hardcoded strings in export templates

