  Phase 3: Simplify the Node UX

  Problem Statement

  The IdeaCard has accumulated 11 actions across 2 customizable decks, plus tags, colors, collapse, pin, pool, focus,
   proximity hover, resize handles, and calendar badges. For new users, this is overwhelming. For power users, most
  actions are rarely used. The dual-deck drag-to-customize system is over-engineered for the actual user need.
  Complexity is diluting the canvas-first experience.

  Intended Solution

  Reduce the primary NodeUtilsBar to 5-6 essential actions. Move everything else into a right-click context menu.
  Kill the dual-deck customization. Make the node feel lightweight and fast — a card you think with, not a control
  panel you configure.

  Sub-tasks

  3.1 — Define the essential action set
  - Primary bar (always visible on hover):
    - Generate/Transform (sparkle icon) — the core AI action
    - Connect (link icon) — canvas thinking's key gesture
    - Synthesize (new — from Phase 1, only shows when node has children)
    - Copy content (clipboard icon)
    - Delete (trash icon)
    - More... (opens context menu)
  - Total: 6 actions, single row, no decks

  3.2 — Build context menu for secondary actions
  - "More..." opens a right-click-style context menu with:
    - Tags, Color, Pin, Collapse, Focus, Duplicate, Share, Pool, Image, Attachment
  - Group by category: Edit (tags, color) / View (collapse, focus) / Organize (pin, pool, share, duplicate) / Insert
  (image, attachment)
  - Context menu component: src/features/canvas/components/NodeContextMenu.tsx
  - Same menu triggered by right-click on the node card

  3.3 — Remove dual-deck toolbar system
  - Remove deck1 / deck2 from UtilsBarLayout
  - Remove reorderUtilsBarAction, DeckColumn, useToolbarDrag
  - Remove Toolbar section from Settings panel (or replace with a simple "Reset bar" option)
  - Simplify NodeUtilsBar.tsx to render a flat list of primary actions
  - This removes significant code and test surface area

  3.4 — Clearer heading/prompt UX
  - Add subtle placeholder text in the heading: "Type a prompt or title..." (from string resources)
  - When user presses Enter in heading, show a brief tooltip: "AI generating..." rather than relying on users to
  discover the heading = prompt concept
  - Add a small "AI" badge next to the heading when the node is in ai mode vs note mode

  3.5 — TDD test suite
  - NodeContextMenu.test.ts: renders all secondary actions, keyboard navigation
  - NodeUtilsBar.test.ts: update for simplified 6-action bar
  - Remove all dual-deck related tests (clean deletion)
  - Structural test: verify NodeUtilsBar has ≤6 primary actions

