  Phase 4: Smart Clustering & Canvas Overview

  Problem Statement

  As canvases grow beyond 20-30 nodes, users lose the "peripheral vision" advantage. Everything looks like a flat
  scatter of cards. There's no way to see themes or gaps at a glance. The minimap shows positions but not meaning.
  Spatial proximity is accidental (wherever the user dropped the node) rather than semantic (related ideas near each
  other).

  Intended Solution

  Add AI-powered clustering that suggests groupings based on content similarity, and visual group boundaries that
  make themes visible at any zoom level. Add semantic zoom so that zooming out shows an overview of topics rather
  than tiny unreadable cards.

  Sub-tasks

  4.1 — Content similarity scoring
  - Create src/features/ai/services/clusteringService.ts
  - computeSimilarityMatrix(nodes: IdeaNodeData[]) — TF-IDF or embedding-based similarity between all node pairs
  - Reuse existing TF-IDF infrastructure from AI Memory Pool ranking
  - Returns clusters: { clusterId, nodeIds, suggestedLabel }[]
  - Configurable threshold for cluster granularity

  4.2 — AI cluster labeling
  - For each detected cluster, send the node headings/summaries to Gemini
  - AI returns a short label (2-4 words) describing the theme
  - Labels displayed on canvas as floating group headers

  4.3 — Visual cluster boundaries
  - Render translucent colored rectangles behind clustered nodes (convex hull of node positions + padding)
  - Colors auto-assigned from a harmonious palette (CSS variables)
  - Cluster label positioned at top-left of the boundary
  - Boundaries update reactively as nodes are dragged

  4.4 — "Suggest clusters" action
  - Button in workspace controls: "Cluster" (or magic wand icon)
  - Runs clustering → shows preview overlay with suggested boundaries
  - User can accept (nodes auto-arrange into tight clusters) or dismiss
  - Accepted clusters become persistent group metadata on the workspace

  4.5 — Semantic zoom
  - At zoom < 50%: node cards collapse to show only heading text (larger font, no body)
  - At zoom < 25%: nodes collapse to colored dots, cluster labels become prominent
  - Smooth transition between zoom levels
  - Implementation: conditional rendering in IdeaCard based on viewport zoom from ReactFlow

  4.6 — TDD test suite
  - clusteringService.test.ts: similarity scoring, cluster detection, edge cases (1 node, all identical, all
  different)
  - ClusterBoundary.test.ts: renders hull, updates on drag, respects theme colors
  - IdeaCard.semanticZoom.test.ts: renders heading-only at low zoom, dot at very low zoom

