  Phase 5: Image Intelligence (Simplified)

  Problem Statement

  Users upload images to nodes but the AI can't "see" them — only text documents get analyzed. This limits the canvas
   to text-based thinking when visual artifacts (screenshots, diagrams, photos of whiteboards) are a huge part of
  knowledge work.

  Intended Solution

  Extend the existing document analysis pipeline to handle images. Keep it simple — no SparkleIcon, no toolbar toggle
   duplication, no "attachments" rename. Just: upload image → AI analyzes it → insight node appears (same as
  documents).

  Sub-tasks

  5.1 — Fix imageDescriptionService MIME bug
  - Replace hardcoded 'image/jpeg' with blob.type || 'image/jpeg' in imageDescriptionService.ts
  - One-line fix, high impact

  5.2 — Route images through the document analysis pipeline
  - In useDocumentAgent.ts, extend analyzeAndSpawn to accept image blobs
  - For images: call describeImageWithAI() to get parsedText, then run standard analysis
  - No need to split into analyzeOnly / spawnInsightNode — the current coupled flow works fine for this use case
  - Respects existing autoAnalyzeDocuments toggle and premium gate

  5.3 — Wire image upload to analysis trigger
  - In useIdeaCardImageHandlers.ts, after successful image insert, trigger analysis if autoAnalyzeDocuments is on
  - Store image AttachmentMeta on node data for extraction caching (minimal extension to document.ts)

  5.4 — TDD test suite
  - imageAnalysis.test.ts: MIME fix, image → analysis → insight node
  - useIdeaCardImageHandlers.test.ts: image upload triggers analysis when toggle is on
  - Structural test: image MIME types accepted in AttachmentMeta

  5.5 — Skip from original plan
  - No SparkleIcon component (insight node auto-creates, same as documents)
  - No toolbar toggle duplication (settings toggle is sufficient)
  - No "documents" → "attachments" rename (low value, high churn)
  - No hasExtraction / insightSpawned transient attributes (unnecessary without SparkleIcon)
  - Net result: ~5 files changed instead of 18

